megacoMib.name: megacoMib

revisions.description: Corrected syntactical errors and some MIB errors
Reworked the entire MIB to add the missing objects and eliminate the ambiguities
Initial Version by Holdridge et al

megacoMib.contactinfo: Postal: Bala Pitchandi UTStarcom Inc 33 Wood Avenue South Iselin, NJ 08830 Phone: +1 (732)452-4457 Email: bs@utstar.com
megacoMib.description: Media Gateway Control (Megaco) Management Information Base (MIB)

MediaGatewayId.name: MediaGatewayId
MediaGatewayId.description: Possible Media Gateway Id that can be used to identify any media gateway uniquely

MediaGatewayLinkId.name: MediaGatewayLinkId
MediaGatewayLinkId.description: Possible Media Gateway Link Id that can be used to identify any media gateway link uniquely

MediaGatewayTermId.name: MediaGatewayTermId
MediaGatewayTermId.description: Possible Termination Id that can be used to identify any media gateway termination uniquely

medGwyLinkIdTable.name: medGwyLinkIdTable
medGwyLinkIdTable.description: This table contains a nextLinkId for each Gateway. It provides the manager with the nextLinkId for use in creating new Gateway Table Entries.

medGwyLinkIdEntry.name: medGwyLinkIdEntry
medGwyLinkIdEntry.description: This table contains the NextLinkId for this Gateway and is indexed by mediaGatewayId.

medGwyNextLinkId.name: medGwyNextLinkId
medGwyNextLinkId.description: The Next Value for a MediaGateway LinkId. Assists the manager in selecting a value for medGwyGatewayLinkId. Using the TestAndIncr syntax, A Manager will 'lock' this variable, ensuring single access.

medGwyGatewayConfigEntry.name: medGwyGatewayConfigEntry
medGwyGatewayConfigEntry.description: Entry holding configuration information about a group of Media Gateway Controllers sharing the same signaling link.

medGwyGatewayId.name: medGwyGatewayId
medGwyGatewayId.description: The unique Media Gateway Id which identifies this media gateway

medGwyGatewayLinkId.name: medGwyGatewayLinkId
medGwyGatewayLinkId.description: The unique link id which identifies the signalling link that this gateway uses to communicate with the Gateway Controller(s).

medGwyGatewayLinkName.name: medGwyGatewayLinkName
medGwyGatewayLinkName.description: A descriptive name of this signalling link / media gateway combination

medGwyGatewayIPAddress.name: medGwyGatewayIPAddress
medGwyGatewayIPAddress.description: The IP address that the Media Gateway Controller will use to communicate with the Media Gateway. The value 0.0.0.0 is returned if the entry is invalid.

medGwyGatewayPort.name: medGwyGatewayPort
medGwyGatewayPort.description: TCP/UDP port number that the Media Gateway Controller will use to communiacte with the Media Gateway. The value 0 is returned if the entry is invalid.

medGwyGatewayEncodingScheme.name: medGwyGatewayEncodingScheme
medGwyGatewayEncodingScheme.description: The encoding scheme that would be used to encode the Megaco messages that are sent/received to/from the gateway controller

medGwyGatewayProtocol.name: medGwyGatewayProtocol
medGwyGatewayProtocol.description: Type of the control protocol in use.

medGwyGatewaySignalingTptProtocol.name: medGwyGatewaySignalingTptProtocol
medGwyGatewaySignalingTptProtocol.description: Type of the transport protocol that is being used to transport the megaco signalling traffic

medGwyGatewayAdminStatus.name: medGwyGatewayAdminStatus
medGwyGatewayAdminStatus.description: The desired state of the gateway. The testing(3) state indicates that no signalling packets can be passed. When a managed system initializes, all gateways start with medGwyGatewayAdminStatus in the down(2) state. As a result of either explicit management action or per configuration information retained by the managed system, medGwyGatewayAdminStatus is then changed to either the up(1) or testing(3) states (or remains in the down(2) state).

medGwyGatewayOperStatus.name: medGwyGatewayOperStatus
medGwyGatewayOperStatus.description: The current operational state of the gateway. The testing(3) state indicates that no signalling packets can be passed. If medGwyGatewayAdminStatus is down(2) then medGwyGatewayOperStatus should be down(2). If medGwyGatewayAdminStatus is changed to up(1) then medGwyGatewayOperStatus should change to up(1) if the gateway is ready to transmit and receive signalling traffic; it should remain in the down(2) state if and only if there is a fault that prevents it from going to the up(1) state

medGwyGatewayLastStatusChange.name: medGwyGatewayLastStatusChange
medGwyGatewayLastStatusChange.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time the associated link entered its current operational status. If the current status was entered prior to the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

medGwyGatewayResetStatistics.name: medGwyGatewayResetStatistics
medGwyGatewayResetStatistics.description: This object can be used to reset all statistics collected for this media gateway link so far. Statistics will be reset when the object is SET to 'reset'. Upon reset, the agent changes the value of this object to 'notApplicable'.

medGwyGatewayRowStatus.name: medGwyGatewayRowStatus
medGwyGatewayRowStatus.description: This is used to create new rows in this table, Modify existing rows, and to delete existing rows.

medGwyGatewayControllerTable.name: medGwyGatewayControllerTable
medGwyGatewayControllerTable.description: List of the Media Gateway Controllers that are managed in the network

medGwyGatewayControllerEntry.name: medGwyGatewayControllerEntry
medGwyGatewayControllerEntry.description: Entry holding information about an individual Media Gateway Controller.

medGwyGatewayControllerId.name: medGwyGatewayControllerId
medGwyGatewayControllerId.description: An unique identification number that is assigned to the gateway controller by the manager

medGwyGatewayControllerIPAddress.name: medGwyGatewayControllerIPAddress
medGwyGatewayControllerIPAddress.description: The IP address of the Media Gateway Controller. The value 0.0.0.0 is returned if the entry is invalid.

medGwyGatewayControllerPort.name: medGwyGatewayControllerPort
medGwyGatewayControllerPort.description: TCP port of the Media Gateway Controller. The value 0 is returned if the entry is invalid.

medGwyGatewayControllerAdminStatus.name: medGwyGatewayControllerAdminStatus
medGwyGatewayControllerAdminStatus.description: The desired state of the gateway. The testing(3) state indicates that no signalling packets can be passed. When a managed system initializes, all gateways start with medGwyGatewayControllerAdminStatus in the down(2) state. As a result of either explicit management action or per configuration information retained by the managed system, medGwyGatewayControllerAdminStatus is then changed to either the up(1) or testing(3) states (or remains in the down(2) state).

medGwyGatewayControllerOperStatus.name: medGwyGatewayControllerOperStatus
medGwyGatewayControllerOperStatus.description: The current operational state of the gateway controller. The standby(3) state indicates that it is in the standby mode and no signalling packets can be passed. If medGwyGatewayControllerAdminStatus is down(2) then medGwyGatewayControllerOperStatus should be down(2). If medGwyGatewayControllerAdminStatus is changed to up(1) then medGwyGatewayControllerOperStatus should change to up(1) if the gateway contoller is ready to transmit and receive signalling traffic; it should remain in the down(2) state if and only if there is a fault that prevents it from going to the up(1) state

medGwyGatewayStatsEntry.name: medGwyGatewayStatsEntry
medGwyGatewayStatsEntry.description: Entry holding statistics about a group of media Gateway/signalling link pair

medGwyGatewayNumInMessages.name: medGwyGatewayNumInMessages
medGwyGatewayNumInMessages.description: Total number of messages received on the link.

medGwyGatewayNumInOctets.name: medGwyGatewayNumInOctets
medGwyGatewayNumInOctets.description: Total number of octets received on the link.

medGwyGatewayNumOutMessages.name: medGwyGatewayNumOutMessages
medGwyGatewayNumOutMessages.description: Total number of messages sent on the link.

medGwyGatewayNumOutOctets.name: medGwyGatewayNumOutOctets
medGwyGatewayNumOutOctets.description: Total number of octets sent on the link.

medGwyGatewayNumErrors.name: medGwyGatewayNumErrors
medGwyGatewayNumErrors.description: Total number of signaling-level errors encountered. Includes, but is not limited to, number of bad messages received, number of failures to sent a message and number of other errors.

medGwyGatewayNumTimerRecovery.name: medGwyGatewayNumTimerRecovery
medGwyGatewayNumTimerRecovery.description: Total Number of timer recovery events since the statistics was last reset. This reflects all protocol timers that are supported (For Megaco, T - start timer, S - short timer, L - long timer, and Z - long duration timer etc)

medGwyGatewayTransportNumLosses.name: medGwyGatewayTransportNumLosses
medGwyGatewayTransportNumLosses.description: Number of times a transport link was lost (excluding switch-over cases). A link loss is defined as loss of communication with the entity (MGC) due to hardware/transient problems in the interface or other related hardware/software

medGwyGatewayTransportNumSwitchover.name: medGwyGatewayTransportNumSwitchover
medGwyGatewayTransportNumSwitchover.description: Number of times when the signaling was switched over to an alternative link. This includes switchover due to the Handoffs initiated by the gateway controllers

medGwyGatewayTransportTotalNumAlarms.name: medGwyGatewayTransportTotalNumAlarms
medGwyGatewayTransportTotalNumAlarms.description: Total number of all alarms issued for the transport layer.

medGwyGatewayTransportLastEvent.name: medGwyGatewayTransportLastEvent
medGwyGatewayTransportLastEvent.description: Last event reported by the transport layer.

medGwyGatewayTransportLastEventTime.name: medGwyGatewayTransportLastEventTime
medGwyGatewayTransportLastEventTime.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time when the event specified by mediaGatewayTransportLastEvent occured. If the last event occured prior to the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

medGwyGatewayLastStatisticsReset.name: medGwyGatewayLastStatisticsReset
medGwyGatewayLastStatisticsReset.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time when the statistics were reset. If the reset occured prior to the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, this object contains a zero value.

medGwyTermIdTable.name: medGwyTermIdTable
medGwyTermIdTable.description: This table contains a nextTerminationId for each Gateway. It provides the manager with the nextTerminationId for use in creating a new TerminationsTable Entry.

medGwyTermIdEntry.name: medGwyTermIdEntry
medGwyTermIdEntry.description: This table contains a nextTerminationId for each Gateway, and is indexed by mediaGatewayId.

medGwyNextTerminationId.name: medGwyNextTerminationId
medGwyNextTerminationId.description: The Next Value for a MediaGateway TerminationId. Assists the manager in selecting a value for medGwyTerminationId. Using the TestAndIncr syntax, A Manager will 'lock' this variable, ensuring single access.

medGwyTerminationsTable.name: medGwyTerminationsTable
medGwyTerminationsTable.description: This table contains information about terminations in a media gateway. It is a list of terminations. The number of entries equals to the total number of terminations for all contexts in a gateway.

medGwyTerminationsEntry.name: medGwyTerminationsEntry
medGwyTerminationsEntry.description: It contains objects that describe a termination.

medGwyTerminationId.name: medGwyTerminationId
medGwyTerminationId.description: An unique identification number that is assigned to the termination by a media gateway. This is the TerminationId that would be used in the protocol messages that are sent from the gateway

medGwyTerminationName.name: medGwyTerminationName
medGwyTerminationName.description: A descriptive name that would describe this termination and its use. For example, 'emergency-ds0-1' indicating that this termination is reserved as an emergencey DS0 channel

medGwyTerminationAdminStatus.name: medGwyTerminationAdminStatus
medGwyTerminationAdminStatus.description: The desired state of the termination. The testing(3) state indicates that no connections can be created for this termination. When a managed system initializes, all terminations start with medGwyTerminationAdminStatus in the out-of-service(2) state. As a result of either explicit management action or per configuration information retained by the managed system, medGwyTerminationAdminStatus is then changed to either the in-Service(1) or testing(3) states (or remains in the out-Of-Service(2) state).

medGwyTerminationOperStatus.name: medGwyTerminationOperStatus
medGwyTerminationOperStatus.description: The current operational state of the termination. The testing(3) state indicates that it is in the testing mode and no connections can be created on it. If medGwyTerminationAdminStatus is out-of-service(2) then medGwyTerminationOperStatus should be down(2). If medGwyTerminationAdminStatus is changed to up(1) then medGwyTerminationOperStatus should change to up(1) if the termination is ready to accept connections; it should remain in the down(2) state if and only if there is a fault that prevents it from going to the up(1) state

medGwyTerminationInterfaceIdentifier.name: medGwyTerminationInterfaceIdentifier
medGwyTerminationInterfaceIdentifier.description: A number that uniquely identifies the interface in the physical gateway. This is the ifIndex in the ifTable, that this termination would be using to communicate to other gateways

medGwyTerminationPropertyProfileId.name: medGwyTerminationPropertyProfileId
medGwyTerminationPropertyProfileId.description: This determines the profile of the termination which determines what kind of capabilities this termination has. This is an index into the medGwyPropertyProfileTable which identifies all the profile that are available

medGwyTerminationRowStatus.name: medGwyTerminationRowStatus
medGwyTerminationRowStatus.description: This is used to create new rows in this table, Modify existing rows, and to delete existing rows.

medGwyPropertyProfileTable.name: medGwyPropertyProfileTable
medGwyPropertyProfileTable.description: This table contains a list of the properties supported in a Profile. A Manager builds a Profile of properties, then ties each termination to a defined profile

medGwyPropertyProfileEntry.name: medGwyPropertyProfileEntry
medGwyPropertyProfileEntry.description: Each row represents a default property of the Property Profile N-entries per mediaGatewayId/PropertyId, one entry per property.

medGwyPropertyProfileId.name: medGwyPropertyProfileId
medGwyPropertyProfileId.description: This PropertyProfile Identifier uniquelyidentifies this set of properties. This is the value each termination would refer, when they would like to support all the properties in this profile

medGwyPropertyProfileIndex.name: medGwyPropertyProfileIndex
medGwyPropertyProfileIndex.description: This is the index to the PropertyProfile This is just a 'counter' through the medGwyPropertyProfile Table. ie, property=1 property=2 etc.

medGwyPropertyProfileProperty.name: medGwyPropertyProfileProperty
medGwyPropertyProfileProperty.description: The Property supported by this Profile. This is an Object ID (OID) defined in a package MIB to identify a Particular property (such as AnalogLines, Tones etc).

medGwyTermPropertyProfileStatus.name: medGwyTermPropertyProfileStatus
medGwyTermPropertyProfileStatus.description: used to create new rows in this table, modify existing rows, and to delete existing rows.

medGwyReceivedElement.name: medGwyReceivedElement
medGwyReceivedElement.description: The element name received in a megaco message. For example, 'eventDescriptor' is one such element that could be sent with the notifications

medGwyLinkStatusChange.name: medGwyLinkStatusChange
medGwyLinkStatusChange.description: This notification indicates that operational status of a media gateway control link has changed.

medGwyInvalidControllerAddress.name: medGwyInvalidControllerAddress
medGwyInvalidControllerAddress.description: This notification indicates that a message was received from a controller that did not match any of the valid controller IPAddress-es configured in medGwyGatewayControllerTable

medGwyInvalidTerminationId.name: medGwyInvalidTerminationId
medGwyInvalidTerminationId.description: This notification indicates that a message was received from a controller that contained a TerminationId that did not match any TerminationId in the TerminationsTable. TerminationId is found in the OID of the medGwyTerminationName Object.

medGwyInvalidPackageElement.name: medGwyInvalidPackageElement
medGwyInvalidPackageElement.description: This notification indicates that a message was received from a controller that contained an event, signal, or descriptor that was not recognized for the package.

medGwyTerminationStatusChange.name: medGwyTerminationStatusChange
medGwyTerminationStatusChange.description: This notification is sent when a termination changes status.

medGwyGatewayHandoff.name: medGwyGatewayHandoff
medGwyGatewayHandoff.description: This notification is sent when a gateway is handed off to a different gateway controller either due to a apparent MGC failure or due to a MGC-enforced condition

medGwyProtocolError.name: medGwyProtocolError
medGwyProtocolError.description: This notification is sent when a protocol error is detected in the messages received from the 'configured' gateway controllers

medGwyCompliance.name: medGwyCompliance
medGwyCompliance.description: Compliance statement for entities which implement the MEGACO-MIB.

medGwyConfigGroup.name: medGwyConfigGroup
medGwyConfigGroup.description: This group contains of all the configuration Information for a Media Gateway. This group is mandatory for any implementation managing a media gateway or a group of media gateways

medGwyStatsGroup.name: medGwyStatsGroup
medGwyStatsGroup.description: This group contains of all the statistics Information for a Media Gateway. This group is mandatory for any implementation managing a media gateway or a group of media gateways

medGwyGWControllerGroup.name: medGwyGWControllerGroup
medGwyGWControllerGroup.description: This group contains of all the configuration Information for a Media Gateway Controller. This group is mandatory for any implementation managing a media gateway controller or a group of media gateway controllers. It is also mandatory for implementations managing media gateway(s)

medGwyNextIdGroup.name: medGwyNextIdGroup
medGwyNextIdGroup.description: Agent provides NextId's to the Manager to assist in selecting and creating new table entries. This group is optional for all the implementations. But when it is not implemented, it is the manager's responsibility to uniquely determine these ids

medGwyNotificationsGroup.name: medGwyNotificationsGroup
medGwyNotificationsGroup.description: This group contains notifications that an entity implementing the Media Gateway(s) will send. This group is mandatory for all implementations that are managing a media gateway or a group of media gateways
